## Context

RDJ-26561 R&R (tracker 0274), remark ED-05. The editor requires, with the
revised paper: a summary of the main revisions and a point-by-point reply to
the referee report and to the editor's own letter. Deadline three months from
the decision (~2026-10-20); email Cédric Chambru if slipping. The paper will
not necessarily return to the referees.

## Relevant files

- `deliverables/data-paper/revision-rdj26561/ledger.dedup.jsonl` — the
  point-by-point skeleton (one reply per distinct remark)
- Sibling tickets 0275–0282 — each drafts its response-letter bullet on close
- Œconomia response-letter machinery (ticket 0152 lineage) — reuse the format
- `~/CNRS/papiers/sent/RDJ4HSS_Curated_Corpus_Climate_Finance/` — where the
  final letter and resubmission record file

## Actions

1. Assemble the point-by-point reply from the ledger: every distinct remark
   gets a reply citing the revision that answers it (or a reasoned decline).
2. Write the summary of main revisions.
3. Voice: first person singular, aligned before showing the author
   (letter-voice norm).
4. Package the resubmission (revised PDF, reply, summary) and hand to the
   author for submission via the journal platform; file records in the
   papiers/ track folder.

## Test

- Coverage-style check: no ledger remark without a reply paragraph.

## Verification

- [ ] Point-by-point reply covers all 15 distinct remarks
- [ ] Author reviewed and approved the letter before submission

## Invariants

- Letters are the author's voice; nothing submitted without author sign-off.

## Exit criteria

- [ ] Response letter + summary of revisions finalized
- [ ] Resubmission package delivered to the author before the deadline
- [ ] Submission record filed under papiers/sent/ track folder
